This paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically edge colouring of graphs with maximum degree three. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also involves computational geometry, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and graph algorithms, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
